This paper is likely to belong to the machine learning (cs.LG) sub-category as it introduces a new machine learning technique, the support tensor train machine (STTM), which extends traditional vector-based machine learning techniques to their tensor forms. Additionally, the paper discusses the limitations of the conventional support vector machine (SVM) and proposes a solution to overcome these limitations. The paper may also be relevant to the artificial intelligence (cs.AI) sub-category as it introduces a new technique for processing and analyzing data. The paper may also be relevant to the computer vision (cs.CV) sub-category as it discusses the use of tensors to capture data structure, which is relevant to image and video data. The paper may also be relevant to the neural networks (cs.NE) sub-category as it proposes a new machine learning technique that can be used for training neural networks. Finally, the paper may be relevant to the data structures and algorithms (cs.DS) sub-category as it discusses the use of tensor trains, which are a type of data structure used for representing high-dimensional tensors.
